Our fambam loves their chicken broccoli and vegi springrolls. We never get bored of sawasde thai night in our household
Had a great experience in here with my friend. The food came quickly and the service is just excellent. Prices are convenient.
Food is perfect every time.
If you want good curry, this is the place to go.
Love Sawasde! My favorite is their scarlet curry. Always spicy, when you ask for it, delicious and good portions!
Delicious Thai takeout spot. I always get the pad see eew
Low key fantastic Thai food that is inexpensive! I ordered the panang curry and pad thai...so impressed!
Very rude lady who works at the front, always rolling her eyes and scoffing. Would avoid by all means.
Delivery from Sawasde is mind-blowingly delicious. Try the eggplant with chicken, or the pad kra prow. The service is always honest and professional, the food fresh and a flavor explosion.
20200929::new spot for trying pad thai, not bad
Fast, friendly, delicious!
My preferred spot for Thai food. Food with real quality ingredients.  I'll return with my friends. The bill was reasonable. Food is like a restaurant in Louisville I loved.
I loved my Food !! I ordered the Drunken Noodle some Spring Rolls and Chicken sauté. Everything was so great like I can explain how bomb this food was especially the drunken noodle.
Delicious curry
Really good food but slightly pricy. Do not order anything spicy if you can not handle it because they're not joking with their spicy.
They offer a nice variety of fresh food. I like dining here. Staff members are always super friendly, prices are affordable and the spot is always kept clean.

Some of the best Thai food I’ve had in this city. It’s takeout only... and I would love for them to one day have the space to sit and have a meal (post COVID) but in the meantime, this is about as good as it gets when it comes to Thai food in NYC. Their curries have so much flavor.. and their coconut mango sticky rice is just about the most delicious thing on this planet.
The food is delicious.

First off I want to say that Sawasde has some of the best Thai food I’ve ever eaten, it has been a godsend during quarantine. That being said, today, after ordering from them multiple times I received a phone call from someone at the restaurant telling me that if I tried to order from them again, they would cancel my order, because I “live too far” and the delivery person “doesn’t like coming to my apartment.” I, according to seamless, live within their delivery radius, it’s only a mile away! It’s absolutely asinine, especially in a time like this, that they would refuse someone who is actively giving them money. When the delivery man arrived he was angry and said “Never again! This is the last time! I will not deliver here again!” He was extremely rude and practically threw my food at me.  You put a sour taste in my moth Sawasde. This is so stupid!!!
Delicious food, red curry fully recommended it is tasty and you will get value for money. If you would take it to go with a dish will suffice for two people eating regular portions. Enjoy it!
Great spot to eat some food when in a rush. Their customer service is quick, pricing is reasonable, excellent character. Highly recommended
Delicious food. Pad Thai, corn fritters and spring rolls are satisfying.
Food is really good. Yammy... ☺ ☺ ☺

Fair is fair. Editing this review because I realize businesses live or die by these . At first my original review was 3 stars  but after trying them a few more times they earn an extra star.  This place has a lot going for it. They do a good job of cranking out orders in about 10 min, the staff is chill and polite, hrs are great and the prices are definitely fair for the portions. Still agree with some of the reviews here. Definitely an element missing when it comes to spices but I think that can be remedied by asking for more of what you want. Still sticking with questioning the quality of  some of the ingredients but when considered to the price and portions it makes sense and does not completely ruin the overall taste. Some dishes are stronger than others fah sure but overall it’s worth it and it hits the spot.
Outstanding Thai food served with gracious politeness. They have only one sit down table (literally) and we were lucky enough to get it. Highly recommended!

We keep meaning to write this review, but we are too busy eating the most amazing Thai food in New York City. I have been to Thailand- this is not an exaggeration. The spices are perfect, the quality of the food is CONSISTENTLY amazing, and nothing on the menu is ever done halfway. You could order the most basic Thai dish and it will be better than anything you've ever ordered. There are no throw aways in this menu. Please do yourself a favor- order from here. I do not care if it means they'll be busier, for I will happily wait hours for it.  (You never will. So fast.) ขอบคุณ, Sawasde Thai Cooking!!!!
I didnt buy nothing from there Just driving by and saw him picking his nose and so busy with it Bon appetit
Plenty of other better thai places in the neighborhood. Do not recommend coming here staff is highly unprofessional.
Do not recommend this place.

Very rude staff always forgets to bring you forks and spoons and if you dare to complain they won't bring you your next order which whatever it is fine there is plenty of thai restaurants in the area but, to not call and have a pregnant lady waiting around for food that is never coming in absolutely unacceptable.
Great
Really solid. I’m not Thai, so maybe not the best judge, but the food is delicious. Very friendly staff. Prices reasonable.
I tried this place already with a friend and I am hooked since then. I enjoy the fantastic character and yummy dishes and beverages. Keep it up.

Congratulations, you've found the best Thai food in Brooklyn. I'm not kidding. I've been going here religiously for years. The staff is comprised of wonderful, sweet people who care about thier craft. As such, the food is to die for. The Massamun curry here has one of the most complex flavor profiles I've ever encountered. The Pad-See Ew is overwhelmingly fantastic and is my regular go-to. Even the little things are perfect here. The appetizers are all incredible. The thai iced tea is worth writing home about. This is the best Thai food in the borough. Seriously. You're in for a treat if you order from them.
Amazing test, great food, friendly staff
The food is good
Fantastic chicken pad Thai!

I ordered from here with great expectations based on the reviews and a recommendation from a local of the area. I will agree with other reviewers that the service was extremely prompt, and the serving size is large but that's about where it ends.  The food itself was mediocre at best. I felt like i ordered from a Chinese restaurant opposed to a Thai restaurant--the food was bland and lacked the authentic spices and flavors which is the main embodiment of Thai food. The shrimp pad Thai I ordered tasted like dry ramen, and I could count the pieces of shrimp it contained on one hand. If you're a genuine Thai food lover--don't expect much ordering from here.
Pineapple curry is dope
Best place to go for lunch, quantity and quality was really good, But twice their soup was stinking , except those two days rest of all my visits were great and tasty.
I dont hate it.I just went in to take a phone call.I dont eat non kosher food.

(Translated by Google) This place has variety of good food, at various prices. It also has many types of drinks.  (Original) Este lugar tiene variedad de buena comida, a varios precios. También tiene muchos tipos de bebidas.

I work in the area on a daily basis and have tried much of the food options in the area. Sawasde is hands down the best Thai food and I'll even go as far to say, best meal you will find. Everything is made to perfection consistently and tastes fresh. Nong and the staff are always very accommodating and friendly. Dishes can all be altered to your liking, down to the smallest detail. Give this restaurant a try, you won't be disappointed.
Yummy Thai food + prompt service!!
Clean food
Excellent establishment . The food can be a bit pricy even when being compared to other Thai spots , but the quality and taste more than compensates for it.
Best pad thai in BK
So tasty! I think about this Thai food all of the time. Wish I lived closer!
Didn’t let me use the bathroom,  despite ordering a full meal

Tiny restaurant with one table that seats two and a few bar stools to sit by the window, but, i think this it the best Thai restaurant in the neighborhood. The larb and drunken noodles are really good. I usually order takeout and have a Thai icetea or coffee while I wait for my food.
Best food I've tasted in a while.
Love there food everything is fresh and well cooked.
The best tai spot around here I'll tell ya that . Spicy nicely and sometimes it is a long wait but thats because "they the best" (Dj Kalid voice) worth the wait believe me 💯
Very tasty. Can't really dine there but the food is delicious
Quick and tasty !
Really good fried rice. The portions for their lunch special appetizers are small.
Absolutely amazing food. The price is reasonable and customer service is even better. Check them out, they won’t disappoint.
Great food. Most dishes were on point but massaman curry was mediocre at best.
Hands down the best Thai food in the Kensington/Ditmas Park area.
Great Thai Food!
Thai cuisine in a nice neighborhood.
The best Thai food! Takeout spot with large potions and great prices. I highly recommend this place.
Spectacular Drunken Man Noodles. Highly recommend.
Great Thai food. Little pricey but maybe that’s just because I always want to order literally everything on the menu. Quick delivery. No real complaints!
Great take-out Thai, spicy and authentic. Beef noodle soup is wonderful.

Wow. Great Pad Kra Prow. Not as spicy as I wanted, but I didn’t ask for extra spice, so that’s my bad. The extra veggies I asked for were bountiful and perfectly cooked. Every carrot had a crunch... no overcooked broccoli or green beans... I couldn’t be happier. Will ABSOLUTELY be ordering again.
Tasty Thai food!
Love this little place. The food is delicious. Recommend the Pad See-Ew.
Best Thai in the area. Fresh food and always busy. Take out and ordering take 15 to 20 minutes which is usual. I would call ahead. I love the green curry here.
Terrific take out Thai food
Dishes here are good and cheap. Nice place to eat after doing Landry.
The Masaman Curry and Pad See Ew is excellent! They also have great customer service.

This restaurant deserves a big thank you for making fresh, non-greasy food and good portions. The pineapple fried rice was full of. Cashews and cabbage and a wonderful mild yellow curry that kept you wanting more! The basil sauté with tofu had 6 kinds of vegetables and light on the oil so you could taste them. The spring rolls (4) were nicely fried and surprisingly non greasy. Took one hour but worth it! Takeaway is probaly quicker than delivery. Just order ahead!
The food is always good, and the people who own it are always great.  Plus the prices are right. Highly recommended.
A little tiny spot in Brooklyn close to the church Avenue train line. I love the food ,and little pricey but the food is good.  Give it a try.

I am sick of their service. They cook really good food but it's nothing when constantly having horrible service. From giving me incorrect orders. To not taking order at 10:40 when the business hours is at 11:30 to 11:00pm. If kitchen closes at 10:30 then put it in the damn brochure and in all marketing and social media. Half the food is already pre cooked..i can walk up and order food 10:45 and still get my food. It happened before but when I call it's always bad service.  You want business or not... you want money or not? Start making improvement in service.

Good food. Great food actually. Fast, fresh and the chicken soup with tomatoes and mushrooms and scallions was just the right kind of spicy. Duck pan fried noodles were awesome as well. Highly recommended, but seating area is small.

The most tasty Thai food in the area, could be also pretty healthy as long as you don't choose the fried rice dishes. Tom-kha soup is my favorite. Good for take away (There's no much place to sit, One table and one hight table).
Excellent food and service! The chicken wings with the sauce is highly addictive!
Really nice Thai place great for take out but not really a dining in place
We got takeout from here and it was ready really quickly and was really tasty. They were friendly too.
Order 20 minutes b4 my lunch break. Waited 53 minutes before the food came. Lunch break over in 7 minutes. U do the math. Not enough food for $16.88
Good tasting Thai food..

This is a no-frills Thai food restaurant. It's really designed for to-go orders. Food is okay, pretty average overall. Not worth a trip out of the way for. There is nothing amazing or unique about the offerings from here.
Small place, barely any seats. Meant to be take out. But has outdoor seating. Food is always great!
Good place
Standard Thai fare - a downgrade on the previous Thai take-away that it replaced.
Great food, fast delivery. Nice portions!

Excellent true Thai cuisine with expedient delivery. I am very fortunate to have such a quality establishment near to my residence or to pick up  right at the Church Avene F train stop or have delivered  --  excellent, well portioned and delicious cuisine.
I've lived here a few years it's the best food in any category for the area. Unfortunately this makes it harder to get my order in because their line is constantly busy.

This place is a hidden gem. Truly delicious and authentic Thai food at very reasonable prices. Everything I had was spot on. The drunken noodles are really well prepared and so is the pad thai, the emerald curry and the chicken and coconut soup. The sticky rice with ripe mangoes is also excellent for a sweet ending to a fiery meal. The food is pleasantly spicy as it should be and they will adjust it if that's not your thing. Highly recommended.
Awesome pick upb spot. Really good drunken noodles.

Small Thai outpost with solid chicken panang curry and delicious curry puffs. Seating is limited with a short bar area and two tables available on the sidewalk, in warm weather, of course. Prices are average.
Perfect pick-up or delivery spot. Try the drunken noodles! Their duck dishes and curries are great as well.

just ordered lunch from here.  Ordered the drunken noodles and it was tasty.  their lunch menu consists of a typical thai dishes such pad thai, pineapple fried rice, pad see ew.  the drunken noodles was spicy and tasty.  pretty much the same from other places I have ordered from.  lunch is about $9 and you get an appetizer, main course, and soda/water.  not bad for the price.  don't bother eating at the location as it's small seating area.  you're better off getting it to go.
Every dish I've had has been great and the spicy food is really spicy! Can't go wrong.
Solid spot. Panang curry is on point.
I like the noodle soup Thai Boat Noodle  with chicken.
